<root>

<name>map()</name>

<category>Math</category>

<subcategory>Calculation</subcategory>

<type></type>

<example>
<image></image>
<code><![CDATA[
size(400, 400);
float value = 25;
float m = map(value, 0, 100, 0, width);
ellipse(m, 200, 10, 10);
]]></code>
</example>

<description><![CDATA[
Re-maps a number from one range to another. In the example above, 
the number '25' is converted from a value in the range 0..100 into
a value that ranges from the left edge (0) to the right edge (width) 
of the screen.
<br/> <br/>
Numbers outside the range are not clamped to 0 and 1, because
out-of-range values are often intentional and useful.
]]></description>

</root>
